This article is a transcript of a press briefing given by Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton aboard Air Force One. The briefing discusses the President's upcoming visit to New Hampshire, where he will tour ARC Energy and hold a town hall meeting at Nashua High School North. The briefing also covers the President's small business proposal, which aims to increase lending to small businesses by providing capital to small banks. Administrator Karen Mills of the Small Business Administration explains the details of the proposal, including a separate lending facility that is not affiliated with TARP. The briefing also touches on the President's intention to meet with the Dalai Lama and his upcoming meeting with governors to discuss the economy and energy issues. The briefing concludes with a mention of a Politico story about the CIA moonlighting for corporations, to which Burton responds that it is not something the President is concerned about.